> Maple syrup is the not-so-secret ingredient that makes tonight's harissa-seasoned carrots so cravable. The sweet, tender carrots are served up bowl-style along with a variety of delightful flavors and textures: turmeric-seasoned couscous, garlicky kale crisps, creamy hummus, and a sprinkling of dried cranberries and walnuts. This dish will have you coming back for bite after bite!

Adjust #oven{} rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat to 350 degrees. Wash and dry produce (except kale).

Remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%ounce}. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into 1⁄4-inch-thick pieces. Quarter @lemon{1}.

Toss kale on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tablespoon}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. (TIP: For easy cleanup, line baking sheet with aluminum foil first.)

Roast on top rack until browned and crisp, ~{13-15%minutes}. (For 4 servings, divide kale between 2 sheets. Roast on top and middle racks, switching rack positions halfway through.)

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @Israeli couscous{3/4%cup} and @turmeric{1/4%tsp}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until fragrant and toasted, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add @veggie stock concentrate{1}, 3⁄4 cup @water{1/2%cup}, and a big pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until liquid has absorbed and couscous is tender, ~{6-8%minutes}. Keep covered until ready to serve.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add carrots, @harissa powder{1/4%tsp}, salt, and pepper. (TIP: If you prefer a milder flavor, use less harissa powder.) Cook, stirring occasionally, until just softened, ~{5-8%minutes}.

Add half the @maple syrup{1%tablespoon} and 2 TBSP water; cook, stirring occasionally, until carrots are lightly browned and tender, ~{3-5%minutes}. Remove pan from heat.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @hummus{1/2%cup}, juice from one lemon wedge, 1 TBSP @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, and 1 TBSP @water{1%tablespoon}. Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff couscous with a #fork{}; stir in a drizzle of olive oil. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide couscous between #bowls{}. Top with kale, carrots, hummus, @dried cranberries{1%ounce}, and @walnuts{1/2%ounce}. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.